In CASING_FRAGMENT_SHADER (SuperbrainScene.tsx), between line 598 ('    vec3 emission = mix(glowColor, irid, 0.5) * fres * 3.0; // Intense glow') and line 600 ('    float alpha = fres * 0.4;'), insert:
    // Interleaved-gradient-noise dither (house idiom, KnowledgeHorizon.tsx:80) —
    // breaks 8-bit banding on the faint cyan ramp; amplitude +/-1/255, sub-perceptual.
    float ign = fract(52.9829189 * fract(dot(gl_FragCoord.xy, vec2(0.06711056, 0.00583715))));
    emission += (ign - 0.5) * (2.0 / 255.0);
This is pure quantization noise-shaping at +/-1/255 — zero look change, only kills banding. Constants are identical to the existing KnowledgeHorizon dither so the grain character matches the rest of the pipeline.

CorticalSignals.tsx:41 — replace
    float live = step(0.0, age) * (1.0 - step(6.0, age));
with
    float live = step(0.0, age) * (1.0 - smoothstep(5.0, 6.0, age));
Identical output for age < 5; over the final second it eases the residual 0.0082 to zero instead of clipping it. Motion preserved, no resting-frame change (waves only exist transiently after events).
